Section 1:
1 L.D. 1265
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
4 STATE OF MAINE
5 SENATE
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 840,
9 L.D. 1265, “An Act to Amend the Laws Governing Public Employee Market Pay Studies
10 and Comprehensive Reviews of the Classification Plan for State Service Positions”
11 Amend the amendment by inserting after the first instructional paragraph the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 3. Funds transfer. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the
14 State Controller shall transfer $2,000,000 on or before June 30, 2027 from the Department
15 of Administrative and Financial Services, Salary Plan program, General Fund account to
16 the unappropriated surplus of the General Fund to provide funding to contract with
17 contractors to complete market pay studies and reviews pursuant to the Maine Revised
18 Statutes, Title 5, section 7061, subsection 4, paragraphs B and C.'
19 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
20 section number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment amends Committee Amendment "A" to add transfer language.
2233 SPONSORED BY: ___________________________________
2244 (Senator ROTUNDO, M.)
2255 COUNTY: Androscoggin
Page 1 - 132LR1702(08)
SENATE AMENDMENT
